        Microfinance is an amazing innovation that helps people in poverty earn a living by starting small businesses.
        <br>
        <br>
        While we love this model, we believe it takes more than money to build a profitable business that really moves the needle. Giving someone a loan and hoping they figure it all out on their own would be challenging anywhere. It’s even harder in regions of extreme poverty where resources are scarce and there are very few good role models.
        <br>
        <br>
        Elevate Africa takes a more holistic approach, inspired by Silicon Valley’s highly successful “startup accelerator” model. We help entrepreneurs succeed by providing them with business training, mentoring, peer networking, seed capital and technology. This model is implemented on the ground with local African business coaches and trainers to ensure that everything we do is culturally relevant and optimized to succeed in each unique region we operate.
        <br>
        <br>
        We have hundreds of successful businesses up and running in Africa today using this model, with new ones being launched every week.
      </p>
